Manchester United are maintaining interest in Borussia Dortmund's Mats Hummels but his father has rejected the possibility of a move this window.

Throughout the past few weeks, speculation has heightened that Hummels would depart to United for £35million but the player has insisted he will see the season through.

Speaking to Sky News in Germany, Hermann Hummels, the World Cup winner's father and agent, said that the centre back will not leave.

