'There is nothing to it,' he said when asked about a potential January transfer.

United have maintained they will move for major targets in January should they become available and Hummels is on their list.

The 26-year-old has failed to replicate the form he exhibited last year though, and Dortmund are enduring a disastrous campaign which has seen them plummet to second bottom of the Bundesliga.

Hummels missed large parts of the opening stages of the season through injury, and has struggled for form. He and his sought-after team-mate Marco Reus resumed training at Dortmund on Wednesday following the winter break.

